{
  "id": "019d286c-c8e3-7462-a4e5-998b0ab8f808",
  "content": "\"description\": \"Design system for personal content (Lim Chun Zhe). Shares structural patterns with corvia brand but uses its own color palette.\"\n\"shared\": {\n  \"components\": {\n    \"card\": {\n      \"borderRadius\": 16,\n      \"padding\": 32\n    },\n    \"insightBox\": {\n      \"bgOpacity\": 0.08,\n      \"borderOpacity\": 0.25,\n      \"borderRadius\": 16,\n      \"padding\": \"24px 28px\"\n    },\n    \"statBox\": {\n      \"borderRadius\": 16,\n      \"padding\": 28,\n      \"textAlign\": \"center\"\n    },\n    \"terminal\": {\n      \"background\": \"#0d1117\",\n      \"borderRadius\": 12,\n      \"fontSize\": 20,\n      \"lineHeight\": 1.7,\n      \"padding\": 24\n    }\n  },\n  \"contentStrategy\": {\n    \"_description\": \"How slides and post description work together. Slides are the primary content vehicle; the post guides readers through the arc.\",\n    \"postDescription\": {\n      \"maxParagraphs\": 8,\n      \"principles\": [\n        \"The post description is a SHORT narrative arc that guides people through the slides, not a standalone essay.\",\n        \"Target 6-8 short paragraphs. Each paragraph maps roughly to 1-2 slides.\",\n        \"Hook → Problem → Solution → Key insight → Messy part (1 sentence, 'slide N has the breakdown') → Proud moment → Dogfooding/meta → CTA.\",\n        \"Reference specific slides when detail lives there: '(Slide 5 has the full breakdown.)'\",\n        \"Keep technical detail light — enough to intrigue, not enough to explain. The slides do the explaining.\",\n        \"Tone: down to earth, developer journey, honest. Not a press release, not a tutorial.\"",
  "source_version": "marketing/design-system.json",
